{% block subject %}
    {% spaceless %}
        Tuscaloosa City Schools Magnet Confirmation: {{ confirmation }}
    {% endspaceless %}
{% endblock subject %}

{% block body_text %}
	Hi {{ email }},

    You recently submitted an application for enrollment in one of the Magnet Programs at Tuscaloosa city Schools for school year {{ enrollment }}.

	Because you are applying to a High School program, a copy of your student’s current transcript must be submitted to the Magnet Program Office in order for your application to be processed further.  Transcripts must be received NO LATER THAN 4:00 p.m. on Friday, February 20, 2015.  Failure to submit transcripts by the deadline will result in your student’s application being rejected.

	The Office of Magnet Programs is located in the Annie C. Merts building located at 1210 21st Avenue, Tuscaloosa, AL  35401.  Questions should be directed to the Office of Magnet Programs at choice@tusc.k12.al.us or by calling the TCS Attendance Office between the hours of 8:30 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. Monday through Friday.

	Also, remember that you must also register your student for Tuscaloosa City Schools enrollment via the Online New Student Registration at Choice.tuscaloosacityschools.com scheduled to begin March 1, 2015.

	For future reference, your confirmation # is {{ confirmation }}. Please retain a copy of this email for your records.

	Please add choice@tusc.k12.al.us to your address list to ensure you receive future status updates of your application.

	This is an automated email message from a mailbox that does not accept replies.  If you have questions about the application process, please email choice@tusc.k12.al.us or call the TCS Attendance Office between 8:30 a.m. and 4:00 p.m., Monday through Friday.

    Thanks,
    Tuscaloosa City Schools Magnet Program
{% endblock body_text %}

